OL,3,CMotoring organisation urges Home
OL,4,CSecretary to appoint 1,000 new 'cops
OL,5,Cin cars'
OL,7,FHome Secretary Yvette Cooper is being
OL,8,Furged to appoint 1,000 new roads
OL,9,Fpolice officers amid fears that many
OL,10,Fdrivers are "getting away" with
OL,11,Fmotoring offences.
OL,13,FThe AA issued the plea after its
OL,14,Fanalysis of Home Office figures found
OL,15,Fthe number of traffic officers in
OL,16,FEngland and Wales has fallen by 1,022
OL,17,Ffrom 5,237 in 2016 to 4,215 in March
OL,18,Fthis year.
