OL,3,CMotoring organisation urges Home
OL,4,CSecretary to appoint 1,000 new 'cops
OL,5,Cin cars'
OL,7,FA survey of its members conducted last
OL,8,Fmonth indicated 57% believe people can
OL,9,Fget away with careless driving due to
OL,10,Fa lack of police presence on the roads.
OL,12,FMany respondents also said other
OL,13,Foffences were going unpunished due to
OL,14,Fthe reduction in the number of roads
OL,15,Fpolice officers, including using a
OL,16,Fhandheld phone behind the wheel (44%),
OL,17,Fdrug driving (42%), not wearing a
OL,18,Fseatbelt (46%) and using a dangerous
OL,19,Fvehicle (43%).
