OL,3,CMotoring organisation urges Home
OL,4,CSecretary to appoint 1,000 new 'cops
OL,5,Cin cars'
OL,7,FJack Cousens, AA head of roads policy,
OL,8,Fsaid: "Be it driving offences or wider
OL,9,Fcrime, public opinion suggests that
OL,10,Ftoo many people are simply getting
OL,11,Faway it.
OL,13,F"It's clear that the public want to
OL,14,Fsee more bobbies on the beat, so the
OL,15,FGovernment's ambition to increase the
OL,16,Fnumber of police officers is welcome.
OL,18,F"We believe there should be a wider
OL,19,Fapproach to tackling crime and that
OL,20,Fmore cops in cars could produce safer
OL,21,Fcommunities as well as safer roads.
