OL,3,CMotoring organisation urges Home
OL,4,CSecretary to appoint 1,000 new 'cops
OL,5,Cin cars'
OL,7,F"A clear and visible presence is a
OL,8,Fdeterrent itself to ensure better
OL,9,Fstandards of driving, as well as
OL,10,Fsending a warning signal to criminals
OL,11,Fthat the chances of being caught are
OL,12,Fhigher than before.
OL,14,F"Most traffic cops catch other crimes
OL,15,Fin the act, such as discovering stolen
OL,16,Fgoods, through routine stops.
OL,18,F"Similarly, a camera can spot the
OL,19,Fspeeding driver, but it can't stop
OL,20,Fthem if they are under the influence
OL,21,Fof drink or drugs.
